        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 3 at 12:34AM CDT until August 3 at 1:15AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1234 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Adrian, or 14
miles west of Vega, moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...70 mph wind gusts and half dollar size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect some tree damage. Damage is likely to mobile homes,
roofs, and outbuildings. Hail damage to vehicles is
expected.

Locations impacted include...
Vega, Adrian, and Simms.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
